Thank you so much for visiting us here at Waeve! Waeve began with friends searching for a better way to buy We live in an exciting era in which we are virtually unlimited when it comes to Gone are the days when women - particularly young, black women - had to purchase from companies that told them how to look, what to wear and what "good hair" We now know that "good hair" and true beauty means expressing yourself exactly the way that you want to - however you want We can and must demand companies that understand that every single person is unique and beautiful and tailor products to what these women actually We aren’t here to try to make you "fit in", we’re here to help you stand Quality hair extensions are one way to do just that - switch up your look, protect your natural hair, and do you - whatever that means to However, the world of hair extensions can be sooo confusing, with so many conflicting terms (virgin, raw, R emy, processed, unprocessed, wefted?!) and a million vendors to choose from, all claiming a million different The truth is, many of these contain misleading information and untruthful classifications about their It s hard to know who to trust and where to When we couldn t find what we were looking for - a hair company that we could trust , that puts the customer first and seeks to make them happy in every way, we decided to start our E nter We are equally concerned with the experience of buying hair as we are with the quality of the We want to make buying extensions Your hair is such an important part of your beauty regimen and your life, so the way you purchase it should reflect It should come on time, in cute packaging, look great, and be able to go wherever you That is what we are all about here at Waeve - delivering you a product and experience that you can trust and will Follow us on insta No, really ...make sure you re in the Enter your email Instagram Twitter LinkedIn YouTube Search © WAEVE Powered by Shopify Close (esc) Loading   Hair here! Whether it’s natural, weave, long, short, curly, straight, black, green – feel good hair means you decide what makes you feel healthy and "Feel Good Hair" is also hair that you can feel good Right now, the human hair industry is not what it should be, or what we believe it could This is for the same reason it is so hard to buy hair – a total lack of transparency in the sourcing and supply of human hair There’s plenty of conflicting information out there about where human hair extensions come from, who is providing them, how they are processed, and what the lives and wellbeing look like for all of the women and men along this We admit that we don’t know everything there is to know about the way human hair extensions make their way to consumers, because no matter how much research you do (and we’ve done a lot ), the market is murky and filled with misinformation and But we also know that a world in which women can switch up their look, have fun with beauty, and gain confidence through ethically sourced hair extensions and products is possible and we want to get Here at WAEVE, we are donating 5% of all profits to Malala Fund to assist in women and girls’ education and empowerment efforts in the countries from which most hair extensions are We believe that providing women and girls with opportunities for education

Sign up for updates and be the first to know sign up for updates © Bolt Labs, All rights ×   Technology Home Technology Research Team Join Us Contact zkChannels Technology zkChannels (formerly Blind Lightweight Transactions - BOLT) builds on the Lightning Network protocol to offer a means to scale transactions while preserving privacy of interactions between participants on the How zkChannels (BOLT) works? Alice and Bob both execute channel initialization on the agreed initial channel balances, in order to derive the channel Alice and Bob transmit these tokens to the payment network along with a funding transaction to escrow the appropriate funds (while obscuring the source of the funds). Once the funds have been verifiably escrowed, then Alice and Bob can establish and activate the payment Alice can pay Bob as many times as desired at using the payment Alice sends a commitment to the wallet contents and a ZK proof along with each With the proof , Bob verifies he received a valid payment on one of his open channels with sufficient balance without being able to identify Alice . If payment is valid, Bob issues a refund token for Alice s new wallet and Alice is able to revoke the previous wallet to prevent double Using blind signatures , Bob returns a signature on Alice s new wallet without knowledge of the If Alice wishes to close the channel, she generates a channel closure message using her refund token and transmits to the payment Applications Micropayments Our techniques enable a payment channel hub of and private micro transactions where the hub learns nothing about the parties The hub is only assured that the fees were paid on each Trading with Centralized Exchanges Trading at centralized exchanges exposes users to a ton of counterparty Payment channels and atomic swap techniques are useful for enabling trades without risking any Like what you ve read? efforts in developing new gene therapies that will slow skeletal muscle degeneration and heart failure to improve the quality of life, increase longevity and reduce the disease burden of Duchenne muscular dystrophy (DMD) and other neuromuscular ABOUT DMD Duchenne muscular dystrophy (DMD) is a severe genetic disorder characterized by progressive muscle degeneration and consequent muscle As a recessive, condition, it almost exclusively affects males – with approximately ,000 individuals affected DMD starts to show its effects during early The boy’s motor functions rapidly deteriorate with disease progression and, by only to years of age, many boys with DMD are Eventually the heart and breathing muscles are compromised, leading to a premature death from heart or respiratory GENE DELIVERY Limitations of Viral Vectors Currently, Gene Therapy for muscle diseases (skeletal & cardiac) has Significant Limitations Virus (AAV) is a common virus used to deliver "fragments" of healthy genes to the cells that contain unhealthy (mutated) AAV has a limited gene size capacity of 5 kilobases (kb), precluding its use for many larger As an example, Dystrophin, the gene responsible for Duchenne muscular dystrophy (DMD) is kb, meaning that only of the dystrophin gene can be "packaged" into These ‘micro-dystrophins’ might provide only partial improvement of muscle AAV is most often restricted to a single administration due to the likelihood of an immune response to the Also, many people already have preexisting immunity to AAV, which may prevent them from ever receiving this gene AAV is not specifically targeted to muscle, so high doses are required to achieve delivery throughout the This may lead to dangerous side It is difficult and costly to manufacture large quantities of OUR SOLUTION A Gene Delivery Platform We have developed a Platform Technology with key features to address the problems posed by AAV administration Our technology does not use viruses to deliver genes to the A delivery method is much less likely to elicit an immune response, enabling repeated dosing over months or We are able to directly target the muscle We have developed antibodies to a specific muscle protein, which binds to the cell and delivers the appropriate gene into skeletal & cardiac This unique technology has application to a wide range of genetic diseases affecting skeletal and or cardiac Importantly, our platform is Not Restricted By Gene OUR TECHNOLOGY Gene Delivery Our Platform Technology consists of proprietary components that are designed to stabilize and effectively deliver genes into We have developed several monoclonal antibodies against a specific muscle target protein that is present in both skeletal and cardiac We have developed other critical functions to ensure proper gene One component condenses the DNA of the gene and protects it from Another component provides stability in the circulation and assists in movement from blood vessels to the A third component provides a linking role that helps to deliver the DNA to the nucleus of the muscle THE MYOSANA THERAPEUTICS TEAM STEVE RUNNELS CEO Steve has more than years of successful and ABOUT Ventures accelerates New Majority entrepreneurs from high potential to high Our programs focus on providing access to markets, management training and We seek to create community and confidence to support the growth of our members – individually and WHAT IS THE PIPELINE PROGRAM? Statistics show that women and entrepreneurs of color struggle to secure capital – debt or equity – in order to grow their Therefore, we have decided that supply chain contracts, technology scouting, and merger and acquisition joint venture opportunities are a more effective and expeditious way to secure valuable capital, increase the value of the company, and help create Ecosystems around the world are experiencing a rise in demand for accelerators that provide resources to scalable businesses corporations are embracing this new model for reducing fixed costs related to the supplier base and supporting open To date entrepreneurs of color are overlooked and underserved in these current More specifically, there is a lack in the market of accelerators focused on supplier diversity and tech scouting, especially for new majority “ The Pipeline Program actively recruits and retains a pipeline of investment ready businesses who can scale through supply chain contracts, tech scouting and M&A JV ” Program Design Ventures will host its inaugural national accelerator program targeting New Majority entrepreneurs in Washington, DC in We welcome entrepreneurs from across the country to Eligible entrepreneurs will be women and people of color who have been in business from years, engaged full time in the business (preferred), have sector experience, are coachable, articulate a willingness to scale, and whose business has customer traction, market validation and evidence of While our preference will be to accept businesses in the $500k to $1.5M range, we will consider entities on either side of the range who we believe can benefit from the The Accelerator Program will couple MBA style coursework with insight on growth strategies across a variety of The cohort will participate in group learning, be segmented by sector for critical strategies, and receive coaching support and access to experts throughout the course of the Our goal is to help entrepreneurs learn what really works in supporting businesses to scale, and how they can embed these practices within their The Accelerator will take place over a period with a intensive residency required in Washington, We will implement a , training program that will focus on fit and addressing the various needs of both product and service The participants will be supported through one on one office hours with experienced entrepreneurs and investors, advice from corporate mentors through partnerships, and access to subsidized services from our professional services support team comprised of legal, tax, accounting and marketing experts Our goal is to help eligible businesses sufficiently prepare to increase contract opportunities and successfully scale their Each entrepreneur will leave the program with an actionable implementation plan specific to their businesses’ growth and The residency program will be book ended with and workshops, virtual mentoring, rigorous evaluation and a major unsolved problem for cancer patients Most cancer therapies are not curative in advanced cancer patients Some cancer therapies never produce a response in the patient (primary resistance) Even if cancer therapies produce a response, the response is often temporary Some cancer cells survive that go on to produce progression (regrowth of tumor) Therapy resistance is a major contributor to cancer deaths Many cancers rely on autophagy to resist treatment, but efforts to block autophagy and overcome therapy resistance have not been successful thus far Pinpoint’s innovative technology focuses on a new target in the autophagy pathway, the PPT1 enzyme, that offers an exciting new approach to overcoming cancer therapy resistance Pinpoint’s inhibitors provide the chemical innovation that increases the potency and specificity of targeting PPT1 and the autophagy pathway We anticipate Pinpoint PPT1 inhibitors will be effective in multiple cancers that have been shown to rely on the autophagy pathway Our Vision: A new class of treatment for cancers Compelling reasons Pinpoint’s PPT1 inhibitors could be for multiple cancers Either genetic or chemical PPT1 inhibition shows significant tumor growth impairment in vivo in multiple In most cancers, PPT1 expression is higher in cancer versus normal tissue, and in metastases versus primary tumors Pinpoint has developed potent and specific PPT1 inhibitors Pinpoint inhibitors produce Single agent antitumor activity Combine well with other agents Enhance immunotherapy, targeted therapy, and chemotherapy in vivo Hydroxychloroquine is a first generation PPT1 inhibitor, used safely in thousands of patients worldwide, that augments the efficacy of cancer therapy in colon cancer, pancreas cancer and melanoma clinical trials Existing data suggest that Pinpoint’s innovative technology may enhance efficacy as compared to hydroxychloroquine, a PPT1 inhibitor, used safely in thousands of patients worldwide, that augments the efficacy of cancer therapy in multiple clinical Targeting PPT1 to block autophagy in cancer As tumors progress, they become more reliant on autophagy for survival PPT1 inhibitors in combination therapy for cancer About Us Pinpoint Therapeutics is developing novel cancer treatment options aimed to specifically inhibit autophagy, a key cell survival and treatment resistance pathway in Pinpoint inhibitors target a recently discovered enzyme in the autophagy pathway called PPT1, which is highly expressed across most These inhibitors could be applied to a broad range of cancers alone or in combination to overcome therapy Further development of these compounds towards clinical drug candidates will be undertaken by Pinpoint Therapeutics to determine the clinical utility of PNH afflicts people per million A PNH patient’s immune system attacks their own RBCs because these cells lacks a key inhibitory protein that is normally found on their This inhibitory protein prevents complement attack in healthy The chronic hemolysis that results causes serious health problems, including blood clots, organ failure, and Complement Pathway Inhibition Attune Pharmaceuticals has discovered novel small molecule inhibitors of a key component of the complement The complement system is an important part of the innate immune system and is comprised of a group of serum proteins that are activated through sequential protease based There are three major pathways of complement activation the classical, the alternative, and the In certain diseases, activation of the complement system results in For example, in hereditary angioedema (HAE), patients are deficient in (C1-inhibitor). The absence of this key inhibitor results in hyperactivation of the classical complement When activated, high molecular weight kininogen is cleaved by plasma kallikrein, releasing high levels of bradykinin, which causes Attune Pharmaceuticals is advancing oral small molecules inhibitors of plasma kallikrein, which will restore normal levels of bradykinin, potentially preventing or reducing the frequency of HAE In the case of paroxysmal nocturnal hemoglobinuria (PNH), a hemolytic anemia, patients are deficient in CD59 (MAC-inhibitory protein) on their red blood CD59 protects these cells from lysis by the membrane attack complex (MAC). In the absence of CD59, the MAC is no longer impeded and attacks the red blood cells when it detects C3b on their While detection of C3b on microbes is a central feature of the alternative pathway, detection on host cells results in Attune Pharmaceuticals is developing oral small molecules that will interfere with the MAC’s ability to locate C3b on the host cells for the prevention of PNH and other Attune Pharmaceuticals West th Street, th Floor New York, NY © Attune All Rights Developed by Synergy Networx   Team – Attune Pharmaceuticals Skip to content Attune Pharmaceuticals Team Programs Investors Media Contact Team Programs Investors Media Contact Team Management Team Board of Directors Scientific Advisory Board Andrew McDonald, , CEO McDonald Attune and has served as CEO since He is also CEO and a Founding Partner of LifeSci Partners, an investor relations and advisory firm specializing in the life Previously, McDonald served as senior biotechnology analyst at Great Point Partners and was the Head of Healthcare Research and a Biotechnology Analyst at ThinkEquity Prior to entering the financial services, Andrew was a senior medicinal chemist Pfizer and Cytokinetics, where he discovered and developed small molecule Andrew received a in organic chemistry from UC Irvine and completed his in chemistry at UC Ira Kalfus, , CMO Kalfus was Chief Medical Officer at Thar Pharmaceuticals until its acquisition by Grunenthal in Kalfus was previously Vice President of Medical Affairs at Lev Pharmaceuticals, where he led the clinical development for Cinryze, the first HAE prophylaxis therapy, approved by the FDA in Upon the acquisition of Lev by ViroPharma in , he consulted on the Cinryze commercial launch and expansion, as well as i

At dNovo, we turn back the How We Turn Back the Clock: Reprogramming You were made by stem cells, and you are maintained by stem Â As we age, our reservoirs of functional stem cells become depleted Â some stem cells die, some become corrupted, and some simply go to sleep for Â At dNovo we aim to solve the aging problem by making new stem cells with our direct reprogramming technology . Â With this technology we can take your skin, blood, or fat and convert them into new stem cells to replace the stem cells you lose as you The Hair Problem Hair Loss: The Stem Cell Problem At dNovo we understand the root cause of hair loss: Hair Stem Cell Loss . Â The two main causes of hair stem cell loss are dihydrotestosterone (DHT)-induced male patterned baldness and hair Â In these cases hair stem cells are killed or converted into cells that no longer produce Â There have been efforts to make new hair stem cells to replace lost hair stem cells but these have largely been unsuccessful to Â As a result, current solutions only slow down or disguise hair loss, but do not treat the underlying stem cell loss Our Solution We Regenerate Your Hair Stem Cells For the first time, we can solve the root cause of hair loss permanently . Â We do this with our reprogramming technology (patent pending) developed by our team of Stanford Â Using a small piece of your skin or even a few drops of your blood, we can potentially generate your own personalized hair stem cells that are compatible with your immune Your new hair stem cells are then used to replace your lost hair stem cells and generate new The Process How It Works Step 1 Cells are collected at our onsite Step 2 dNovoâs proprietary reprogramming factors are Step 3 Hair producing cells are Step 4 Hair producing cells are seeded onto the Step 5 Hair growth visible in Milestones Q2 dNovo Founded We founded dNovo in to solve the problem of age associated stem cell Â Our first objective was curing hair Â We chose hair loss because no one was directly addressing the underlying problem of hair stem cell loss and we had a Â We joined Y Combinatorâs summer class which accelerated our vision of bringing our direct reprogramming technology to the Â Q3 Human Hair Stem Cells Generated Using dNovoâs Proprietary Direct Reprogramming Technology (Patent-Pending) Our first objective was to generate personalized hair stem cells using our direct reprogramming Â In , we were successful in putting together our direct reprogramming system to generate human hair stem cells (patent pending). Â These reprogrammed human cells successfully reactivated the genetic circuitry of native hair stem Â They also performed biochemically as expected of native hair stem Â After demonstrating this breakthrough, we sought to validate the functionality of our newly reprogrammed human hair stem Q4 9 Weeks After Treatment Demonstration of Hair Growth with dNovoâs Reprogrammed Hair Stem Cells We next demonstrated that our reprogrammed human hair stem cells could generate Â To do this, we developed an optimized transplantation procedure to efficiently graft our reprogrammed After optimization, we transplanted our reprogrammed cells to mice and observed promising Â Hair began to sprout 3 weeks after initial treatment, and by the second month, new hair had clearly grown at the treatment With this development, we demonstrated that our reprogrammed human hair stem cells are a viable cure for hair Q2 Human Dermal Papilla Cells Generated Using dNovoâs Proprietary Direct Reprogramming Technology (Patent-Pending) Dermal papilla cells are another important component of the hair Â These cells serve as the signaling center for hair stem cells and promote robust hair In certain cases where the entire hair follicle is depleted, dermal papilla cells are also lost, and so we sought to generate these cells with our direct reprogramming We have now successfully developed the reprogramming system to generate these human dermal papilla cells (patent pending).
